Volume 21, Number 310 (October 3, 1895) (Chroniclingamerica.loc.gov, viewed June 11, 2020). Daily state (Birmingham, Ala.) Birmingham state herald 2692-4269 (DLC) 2020271956 (OCoLC)1157347560"], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2026-05-19T21:37:52.256Z", "group": ["ndnp/newspapers", "united-states-newspaper-directory"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/item/2020271955/", "image_url": [], "index": 5, "language": ["english"], "location": ["alabama", "jefferson county", "birmingham", "united states", "jefferson"], "number": ["1157346438", "2692-4234", "2026-04-13t21:30:13", "online resource", "2020271956", "2020271955"], "original_format": ["newspaper"], "partof": ["birmingham age-herald (birmingham, ala.) 1890-1895 [online resource]", "serial and government publications division", "directory of u.s. newspapers in american libraries"], "publication_frequency": ["daily"], "score": 43.808174, "shelf_id": "ISSN RECORD", "site": ["usnd"], "subject": ["alabama", "jefferson county", "newspapers", "birmingham", "jefferson county (ala.)", "united states", "birmingham (ala.)", "jefferson"], "timestamp": "2026-05-26T21:01:07.415Z", "title": "Birmingham age-herald", "type": ["title"], "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/2020271955/"}, {"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://www.loc.gov/item/2020271956/"], "campaigns": [], "date": "1895", "dates": ["[1895 TO 1897]"], "description": ["Daily (except Monday) Began with volume 21, number 311 (October 4, 1895); ceased with volume 23, number 166 (July 31, 1897). \"Democratic.\" \"Official organ of the State of Alabama and will publish all public & general laws of the state.\" Numbering sequence continues from: Birmingham age-herald. Numbering is irregular. Also issued on microfilm from Bell & Howell, Micro Photo Div.; the Library of Congress, Photoduplication Service. Description based on: Volume 21, number 311 (October 4, 1895); title from masthead (Chroniclingamerica.loc.gov, viewed June 11, 2020). Latest issue consulted: Volume 23, number 166 (July 31, 1897) (Chroniclingamerica.loc.gov, viewed June 11, 2020). Age-herald 2692-4102 (DLC) 2020271954 (OCoLC)664149721"], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2026-05-19T21:37:52.256Z", "group": ["ndnp/newspapers", "united-states-newspaper-directory"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/item/2020271956/", "image_url": [], "index": 6, "language": ["english"], "location": ["united states", "alabama", "birmingham", "jefferson"], "number": ["1157347560", "2026-04-13t21:30:13", "online resource", "2020271956", "2020271954", "2020271955", "2692-4269"], "original_format": ["newspaper"], "partof": ["birmingham state herald (birmingham, ala.) 1895-1897 [online resource]", "serial and government publications division", "directory of u.s. newspapers in american libraries"], "publication_frequency": ["daily"], "score": 43.808174, "shelf_id": "ISSN RECORD", "site": ["usnd"], "subject": ["alabama", "newspapers", "birmingham", "united states", "birmingham (ala.)", "jefferson"], "timestamp": "2026-05-26T21:01:07.415Z", "title": "Birmingham state herald", "type": ["title"], "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/2020271956/"}, {"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://www.loc.gov/item/2020271957/"], "campaigns": [], "date": "1902", "dates": ["[1902 TO 1950]"], "description": ["Daily Began with vol. 28, no. 330 (May 21, 1902); ceased May 13, 1950. Publication suspended with July 12, 1945 issue due to a printers' strike; resumed publication with Aug. 17, 1945 issue. Also issued on microfilm from Bell & Howell, Micro Photo Div.; the Library of Congress, Photoduplication Service. Also published in a weekly ed. Description based on: Vol. 28, No. 330 (May 21, 1902); title from masthead (Chroniclingamerica.loc.gov, viewed June 25, 2020). Latest issue consulted: Vol. 32, No. 200 (November 16, 1905) (Chroniclingamerica.loc.gov, viewed June 25, 2020). Birmingham post Birmingham post-herald"], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2026-05-19T21:37:52.256Z", "group": ["ndnp/newspapers", "united-states-newspaper-directory"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/item/2020271957/", "image_url": [], "index": 7, "language": ["english"], "location": ["united states", "alabama", "birmingham", "jefferson"], "number": ["2026-04-13t21:30:13", "online resource", "2692-6326", "2020271954", "2020271957", "1159902485"], "original_format": ["newspaper"], "other_title": ["Sunday issues for <June 5, 1927-May 7, 1950> published as combined issue with Birmingham news, with title: Birmingham news, the Birmingham age-herald", "Age-herald"], "partof": ["the birmingham age-herald (birmingham, alabama) 1902-1950 [online resource]", "serial and government publications division", "directory of u.s. newspapers in american libraries"], "publication_frequency": ["daily"], "score": 43.808174, "shelf_id": "ISSN RECORD", "site": ["usnd"], "subject": ["alabama", "newspapers", "birmingham", "united states", "birmingham (ala.)", "jefferson"], "timestamp": "2026-05-26T21:01:07.415Z", "title": "The Birmingham age-herald", "type": ["title"], "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/2020271957/"}, {"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://www.loc.gov/item/2019271249/"], "campaigns": [], "date": "1910", "dates": ["[1910 TO 1920]"], "description": ["Weekly, -1920 Began with volume XV, no. 1 (January 8, 1910); ceased in October 1920. \"A farm and home weekly for the states of Mississippi, Alabama, Louisiana, Arkansas, and Tennessee\" 1910- ; \"A farm and home weekly for Alabama, Mississippi, Tennessee and Arkansas\"--1920. Published at Birmingham, Ala. and Memphis, Tenn., -1920. Called \"Central ed.\"--1920. Description based on: Volume XV, No. 1 (January 8, 1910); title from masthead (Chroniclingamerica.loc.gov, viewed September 17, 2019). Latest issue consulted: Vol. XXVIII, No. 13 (March 29, 1913) (Chroniclingamerica.loc.gov, viewed September 17, 2019). Progressive farmer (Birmingham, Ala. : 1920)"], "digitized": true, "extract_time